---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Local Usage and Privacy">
  <h1>Local usage and privacy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Understand how agents use Brna without recording application content or sending usage data away.</p>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>What it is</h2>
    <p>
      The local usage journal records sanitized lifecycle metadata for Brna CLI
      commands, MCP resource reads, and MCP tool calls. It helps identify common
      workflows, latency, errors, interrupted operations, and successful recovery
      sequences. It is distinct from application <code>logs</code> and
      <code>network</code> records and from opt-in replay <code>trace</code> files.
    </p>
    <p>Brna has no automatic usage upload, synchronization, or remote telemetry path.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Inspect and control</h2>
    <pre><code>brna usage status
brna usage path
brna usage summary --since 7d
brna usage summary --json
brna usage export --since 30d --to usage-report.json
brna usage enable
brna usage disable
brna usage clear</code></pre>
    <p>
      Collection is enabled by default during normal local execution and disabled
      by default in CI. <code>DO_NOT_TRACK=1</code> always disables collection.
      <code>BRNA_USAGE_LOG=0</code> disables it explicitly and
      <code>BRNA_USAGE_LOG=1</code> enables it explicitly unless Do Not Track is set.
      Management commands are never themselves journaled.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Exact privacy boundary</h2>
    <p>The journal can store:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>canonical operation and CLI/MCP surface;</li>
      <li>random operation id and locally salted project/session correlation ids;</li>
      <li>Brna version, operating-system family, architecture, and normalized caller name;</li>
      <li>safe option booleans or enums, duration, outcome, stable error code, phase, and coarse counts.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The journal never stores:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>prompts, agent reasoning, or arbitrary non-Brna tool calls;</li>
      <li>selectors, typed values or their length, paths, URLs, device ids, project names, or environment values;</li>
      <li>snapshots, application text, runtime logs, network records, payloads, stdout/stderr, or error messages.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Storage, retention, and export</h2>
    <p>
      Events are append-only daily JSONL files in the platform's per-user state
      directory. Directories and files use private permissions where supported.
      Brna retains 30 days and at most 50 MiB, removes expired files during bounded
      cleanup, and ignores a malformed or truncated line without losing other events.
    </p>
    <p>
      <code>usage summary</code> reports counts, success rate, p50/p95 duration,
      interrupted operations, stable errors, and recovery transitions.
      <code>usage export</code> writes only this aggregate model and collection-size
      metadata. It excludes raw events, event-level timestamps, and all local ids;
      Brna never transmits the exported file.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
